Interface Providers

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, ProvidersTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProvidersStub

    public interface Providers
extends Service, ProvidersTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Providers interface provides methods to configure identity management on a Supervisor. This interface was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        Providers.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String supervisor,
                            java.lang.String provider)
        Returns information about an identity provider configured for a Supervisor. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        An {#link Info} representing the requested identity provider.

        Parameters:
        supervisor - identifier for the Supervisor for which the identity provider is being read. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.Supervisor.
        provider - identifier for the identity provider that is being read. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.identity.Provider.
        Returns:
        instance of Providers.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the given identity provider or Supervisor cannot be found.
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user cannot be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user is missing the System.Read privilege on the Supervisor.

        Providers.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String supervisor)
        List the identity providers configured for a given Supervisor. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        A list of {#link Summary} with details about the identity providers associated with a given Supervisor.

        Parameters:
        supervisor - the Supervisor for which identity providers are being listed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.Supervisor.
        Returns:
        instance of Providers.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the given Supervisor cannot be found.
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user cannot be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user is missing the System.Read privilege on the Supervisor.

      • create

        Providers.CreateInvocation create(java.lang.String supervisor,
                                  ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Create a new identity provider to be used with a Supervisor. Currently, only a single identity provider can be created. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        a unique identifier for the identity provider that was registered. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.identity.Provider.

        Parameters:
        supervisor - the Supervisor for which the identity provider is being registered. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.Supervisor.
        spec - the {#link CreateSpec} describing the identity provider to be registered.
        Returns:
        instance of Providers.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        InvalidArgument - if the @{param.name spec} contains any errors.
        Unsupported - if the specified Supervisor does not exist, or if an identity provider is already configured.
        Unauthenticated - if the user cannot be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user is missing the Namespaces.Manage privilege on the Supervisor.

      • update

        Providers.UpdateInvocation update(java.lang.String supervisor,
                                  java.lang.String provider,
                                  ProvidersTypes.UpdateSpec spec)
        Update an existing identity provider used with a Supervisor. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        provider - the identifier for the identity provider that is to be updated. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.identity.Provider.
        spec - the {#UpdateSpec} to be applied to the identity provider configuration.
        Returns:
        instance of Providers.UpdateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described update operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        InvalidArgument - if the @{param.name spec} contains any errors.
        NotFound - if the given identity provider or Supervisor cannot be found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user cannot be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user is missing the Namespaces.Manage privilege on the Supervisor.

      • delete

        Providers.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String supervisor,
                                  java.lang.String provider)
        Remove an identity provider configured with a given Supervisor. This will result in users no longer being able to log in to either the Supervisor or any of its workload clusters with that identity provider. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.
        Parameters:
        supervisor - the identifier of the Supervisor which is associated with the identity provider being removed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.Supervisor.
        provider - the identifier for the identity provider that is to be deleted. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.identity.Provider.
        Returns:
        instance of Providers.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        NotFound - if the given identity provider or Supervisor cannot be found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user cannot be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user is missing the Namespaces.Manage privilege on the Supervisor.
